Between 2000-2010, Shinae Chun became the Women's Bureau first Asian-American Director and the highest-ranking Korean American in the Administration. Initiatves during the first half of the decad included Girls E-Mentoring in Science,
				Engineering, and Technology (GEM-SET); Group E-Mentoring in Nursing (GEM-Nursing); Women with Disabilities Entrepreneurship; Working Women in Transition; an Employer-Driven Older Women Workers project; Wi$eUp, a web-based electronic mentoring
				curriculum for Generations X and Y women;
